rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0001
rows.name:
Tora, do you have any ingredients
I could work with?

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0002
rows.name:
Just what in the pantry there.
Not much really. Tora sorry!

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0003
rows.name:
It doesn't seem wise to go out and buy
more supplies, so we'll just have to
make do with what we have.

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0004
rows.name: Let's see what we've got, then.

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0005
rows.name:
Glitterspuds, Sumpkins...
Oh, and here's an Oil Oyster and
a single Meaty Carrot.

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0006
rows.name:
And Hot Oranges too!
These aren't bad ingredients at all!

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0007
rows.name:
All foods that can be eaten with no
cooking. That how Tora usually eat!

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0009
rows.name:
We aren't much better ourselves,
you know!

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0011
rows.name:
So what do you think, Homura?
Can you make anything with this?

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0012
rows.name: Yes, I think this should be enough!

rows.label: fev02_210_125_msg0013
rows.name: I'll just use the kitchen, OK?
